<font color="#FF0000">INTRODUCTION TO SITE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jun 13  0:27:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Today 6/13/97, first time I have seen this site.  I hope to continue to visit as often as I can.  I would like to hear from some of you who may have served in the 3rd brigade of the First Cav.  I was in-country 70-71, Quan Loi, Cambodian invasion, Xaun Loc and other places that were of interest to the Cav.  I was a crew chief on a Uh-1H, tail number 68-16334.  Funny how I still remember so many things about that chopper.  I suppose I should after 900 hrs of riding her and still do.  Everytime I hear a chopper go by, I seem to be pulled into the flight and see the war torn areas of Vietnam go by.  It is now almost 30 years and I don't think any of us will ever forget much of what war was all about.  Contrary to one letter I read tonght about Vietnam vets should get a life and forget everything.  Stop using Vietnam as a crutch.<br>
I don't think that is the case by anyones dreams.  We would like to forget but that is not possible.  Unless one has gone through the experience you will never know how much many of us would like to forget.  As to getting on with one's life, that is possible.  I am a high school teacher (20yrs) and the soccer coach for my school.  I feel I have done rather well for myself.  Teacher pay is not much but I like what I do.  I know this note may seem to ramble but later I will write more and maybe give some of my story.  Oh yes, veteran of Desert Storm.    <br>
 <br>

<p><code>-- jwilliams@datasys.net  ( jerry williams) </code><p>


